2026-04-22 | Words Within Two Edits of Dictionary

Question
Return all such valid query words.
	Approach
1.	For each query word:
2.	Compare with each dictionary word  
3.	Count mismatches:
		for each position:
			if characters differ → count++  
4.	If mismatch ≤ 2:
		this query is valid → add to answer  
		break early  
5.	Continue for all queries  
	Time Complexity
	O(Q × D × L)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    vector<string> twoEditWords(vector<string>& queries,
                               vector<string>& dictionary) {
        vector<string> ans;
        for(string &q : queries){
            for(string &d : dictionary){
                int mismatch = 0;
                for(int i = 0; i < q.size(); i++){
                    if(q[i] != d[i]){
                        mismatch++;
                        if(mismatch > 2) break;
                    }
                }
                if(mismatch <= 2){
                    ans.push_back(q);
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Since:
		word lengths are small  
		edit limit is tiny (≤2)  
We can directly:
		count mismatches  
This avoids complex edit-distance DP and keeps solution efficient.
